---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Hero from '../../components/Hero.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';
import { clinicInfo } from '../../utils/clinicInfo';
// ✅ ADD THIS IMPORT
import { HERO_IMAGES } from '../../utils/images';

const breadcrumbItems = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
  { label: 'Patient Education', href: '/patient-information' },
  { label: 'Oral Hygiene Basics', href: '/patient-education/oral-hygiene-basics' },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Oral Hygiene Basics | Dental Care Tips | NextGen Dental"
  description="Learn the fundamentals of good oral hygiene from NextGen Dental. Discover proper brushing techniques, flossing tips, and daily dental care routines."
>
  <Hero
    title="Oral Hygiene Basics"
    subtitle="The foundation of a healthy, beautiful smile"
    images={[HERO_IMAGES.dental1]} 
    height="md"
  />
  {/* 👆 FIXED: Used HERO_IMAGES.dental1 instead of string path */}

  <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbItems} />

  <div class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <article class="prose prose-lg prose-primary mx-auto">
        <h2>The Importance of Daily Care</h2>
        <p>
          Maintaining good oral hygiene is the most important thing you can do for your teeth and gums. Healthy teeth not only look good, but they also make it possible to eat and speak properly. Good oral health is important to your overall well-being.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Proper Brushing Technique</h3>
        <p>
          Brushing twice a day is the first line of defense against tooth decay and gum disease.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Angle:</strong> Tilt the brush at a 45° angle against the gumline.</li>
          <li><strong>Motion:</strong> Use short, gentle strokes. Don't scrub hard!</li>
          <li><strong>Coverage:</strong> Brush the outer, inner, and chewing surfaces of each tooth.</li>
          <li><strong>Time:</strong> Brush for at least two full minutes.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Don't Forget to Floss</h3>
        <p>
          Daily flossing removes plaque and food particles from between the teeth and under the gumline where your toothbrush can't reach. Because tooth decay and gum disease often start in these areas, flossing is essential.
        </p>

        <h3>Diet and Dental Health</h3>
        <p>
          A balanced diet is necessary for your teeth and gums to remain healthy. A diet high in sugar and starches can lead to tooth decay. Limit sugary snacks and drinks, and drink plenty of water to help wash away food particles.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-primary-50 p-6 rounded-lg not-prose mt-8 text-center">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Time for a Checkup?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
            Daily care is vital, but professional cleanings remove the hardened tartar that brushing misses.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
            <Button 
              href="/contact" 
              text="Schedule Cleaning" 
              variant="primary"
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
